From: GRID authors <mohsen.arjmandi@evolutionid.com>
Subject: [Draft PR] [Core] Structured output: let a grammar defer its own
 scheduling while its bitmask is not ready (is_ready hook + RUNNING-loop
 guard + starvation cap)

DRAFT — NOT APPLIED by bench/vllm_grid_patch.py. This is the upstream vLLM
PR that retires the downstream patch site 4 ("grid mask-readiness defer").
Hunks are written against vLLM v0.24.0.

Motivation
----------
The V1 scheduler gates grammar readiness only for WAITING requests
(WAITING_FOR_STRUCTURED_OUTPUT_GRAMMAR). Once a structured request is
RUNNING, every scheduled step fills its bitmask row before sampling
(EngineCore.step: the fill joins before sample_tokens), so a backend whose
next-token mask is still being computed (e.g. on a background thread,
overlapped with the forward pass) stalls the WHOLE batch for that step:
fill time is max()'d against the forward. Backends have no way to say
"skip me this round; give me one more forward window".

Mechanism
---------
1. StructuredOutputGrammar.is_ready() -> bool, default True (non-abstract:
   existing backends are unaffected).
2. Scheduler RUNNING loop: a request whose grammar reports is_ready() False
   is skipped for the step, exactly like the next_decode_eligible_step
   defer at the same position. It is absent from num_scheduled_tokens,
   therefore absent from structured_output_request_ids: no bitmask row is
   filled, no token sampled, KV blocks intact. Relaxed FCFS is already
   tolerated at this loop position (see the num_new_tokens == 0 comment).
3. Starvation cap: a per-request deadline (GRAMMAR_DEFER_CAP_S, default
   0.1 s) forces scheduling after the cap; fill_bitmask then blocks on the
   grammar exactly as today. Deadline entries are popped whenever the
   request is scheduled; a request aborted while deferred leaves at most
   one stale dict entry (bounded by max_num_seqs; can be cleaned in
   _free_request if reviewers prefer).

Soundness: the skipped request receives no mask and no token that round;
when scheduled it always gets the exact mask — no approximation anywhere.
An empty schedule step is already legal (same path WAITING-grammar polling
uses).
